What you need to know:

Ndungú said the world could not have asked for more with the women’s Marathon World Record holder, Brigid Kosgei, World Marathon champion Ruth Chepng’etich and former London Marathon champion, Vivian Cheruiyot in the mix.“I am putting my money on all Kenyans. Whoever wins let it be a Kenyan. That will be my joy,” said Ndungú, who was quick to note that Ugandan athletes were fast gaining inroads into Kenya’s strong hold.